It’s not luck, we work hard over here! And yes there are times when I feel like I have no more left in me and that’s when @iamprx reminds me of “MY WHY, MY MORE”. I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again, the best therapy I’ve done for both my mental and physical well being has been working out, showing up, and getting it done. Won’t lie, it’s not easy showing up for myself everyday but I’m getting  there and I’m grateful to have accountability partners who don’t take it easy on me and push me to go beyond my comfort and limits. 

So Mama this is for you, the you that feels discouraged, heartbroken, exhausted, depressed, with low self esteem, uncomfortable in your body, YOU ARE NOT ALONE. I was exactly where you are today one year ago, at the lowest of lows, I know you may feel like the walls are caving in and you can’t even catch your breath, just remember this too is TEMPORARY and shall pass. You are stronger than you know, more capable than you can imagine, and you just need to find your light again, one day at a time, show up for you, take care of you, and everything will fall back into place, I promise you!!! What you are not allowed to do is give up on you, YOU ARE ALL YOU NEED! 

Love & Light 

And if y’all need to vent, slide into my DM, let me be your motivation 🤍💛🤍
